author: Inside Edition
description: A man was dragged from behind the wheel of his luxury car by three robbers brandishing guns. They were determined to steal his Swiss watch worth more than $600,000. The victim fought back and one of the robbers was sent sprawling, but the robbers got away with the watch. They knew about Richard Mille watch because the victim posted a video of himself wearing it on Instagram just hours earlier. Inside Edition went with him to the parking garage in California where he was attacked.
title: Robbers Drag Man Out Of Car And Steal His $600K Watch

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump admitted the entire east wing of the White House is being torn down and historians and former East Wing staffers are in shock. In its place will rise a massive ballroom. The price tag has grown from $200 million to $300 million, funded by 37 private donors, including Google, Amazon, Apple, Meta, Microsoft, and Caterpillar. Trump has talked about the ballroom for years. Trump's allies are brushing off the criticism.
title: President Trump Says White House's Entire East Wing Is Being Torn Down

author: Inside Edition
description: Patrick Sullivan, his wife Cynthia, and their son Tyler sailed from Cape Cod last weekend and anchored off the coast on Naushon Island. They were woken up by their dog warning them of a fire on board their boat. They leapt into the water and swam to a cove on a little-known island. The dog died after saving the family. Tyler found the boat's radio washed up on the beach and shouted "Mayday!" They were rescued by the Coast Guard and medevaced to a hospital.
title: Family Rescued From Little-Known Island After Boat Catches Fire

author: Inside Edition
description: A father arrested after leaving his 2-year-old daughter in a hot car to die has pleaded guilty to her murder. Christopher Scholtes frantically called 911 after finding little Parker unresponsive on a hot day outside his home in Arizona. On a police bodycam, the dad told police he left his daughter in the car to nap. Prosecutors say he left the little girl in the car for more than three hours. His wife, who is a doctor, is the one who found Parker after arriving home.
title: Father Pleads Guilty To Murder After Toddler Dies In Hot Car

author: Inside Edition
description: A jogger ran past a front yard display in Salinas, California, and punched one of the witch decorations. She ran off back to her jog, but she returned once again and punched out the other two witches. Could there be a misunderstanding? Video from a few days earlier appeared to show the same woman punching the decorations. Tonya Sampognaro put up the hand-made witches. She spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Halloween Grinch Punches Caught On Camera Punching Decorations

author: Inside Edition
description: Two-year-old Lilah Smoot has been battling an aggressive form of stage 4 brain cancer. Mom Katelynn, dad Tyler, and baby brother William have been documenting her journey with her. One thing that has gotten Katelynn through her toughest days is Taylor Swift. The family was surprised when the singer herself donated $100,000 to their GoFundMe page to help with medical costs. For further information about their GoFundMe, click this link: https://bit.ly/3Jbwgjs
title: Family Receives Very Special Gift From Taylor Swift

author: Inside Edition
description: It was a final bow on an historic career as Misty Copeland performed her last show with the American Ballet Theatre in New York. A star-studded audience, which included Oprah Winfrey, turned out to watch. The event coincided with the annual fall gala at Lincoln Center. It was actually Copeland's first time taking the stage in about five years as she's taken time away from ballet to have and raise her son. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Misty Copeland Takes Stage For Last Time As Principal Ballerina In New York

author: Inside Edition
description: Samantha Peterson crashed a car into a horse-drawn buggy used by a local Amish community, leaving two children dead and two others injured.
title: Woman Sentenced After Urging Twin Sister To Take Fall For Amish Buggy Crash #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Sonya Massey was shot to death in her home in 2024 by a deputy sheriff during a routine 911 call. The officer, Sean Grayson, is on trial Wednesday for her murder.
title: Former Cop's Murder Trial Begins #shorts
